{"type":"text","timestamp":1773435581785,"sessionID":"ses_3170615c1ffe6qPm6NgPYs8fxK","part":{"id":"prt_ce8ff3c91001GjvsgCoQp6WMwd","sessionID":"ses_3170615c1ffe6qPm6NgPYs8fxK","messageID":"msg_ce8ff33c4001NrKyy14575u7tP","type":"text","text":"All done. Here's a summary of what was accomplished:\n\n## Summary\n\n### 3 commits on `feature/test-arg-parsing`:\n\n1. **`fix(test-arg-parsing): fix broken tests for features→tasks alias and missing properties`**\n   - Fixed 12 broken tests where `features` alias resolution was expected to return `\"features\"` but correctly returns `\"tasks\"`\n   - Fixed `result.features` → `result.tasks` (correct CLIArgs property name)\n   - Fixed `result.version` → `result.tag` (`--version` is not a parsed flag; `--tag` is)\n   - Added tests for the features→tasks alias resolution\n\n2. **`fix(test-arg-parsing): use requireValue() for --tail flag to prevent OOB access`**\n   - Fixed a real bug in `src/index.ts` where `--tail` used `args[++i]` directly without bounds checking\n   - Changed to use `requireValue(arg)` for consistent error handling (matches all other value-consuming flags)\n\n3. **`feat(test-arg-parsing): add comprehensive CLI arg parsing edge case tests`**\n   - Added 115+ new test cases (176 total, up from 58) covering all scenarios from the task spec:\n     - **Command alias resolution**: All 16 COMMAND_ALIASES entries verified\n     - **Subcommand alias resolution**: All 10 SUBCOMMAND_ALIASES entries, plus combined aliases (`t ls`, `t a`, `t ss`, `t sp`, `t sd`)\n     - **Boolean flags not consuming next positional**: 15 boolean flags tested (`--dry-run`, `--all-ready`, `--force`, `--interactive`, `--no-tui`, `--auto-push`, `--requeue`, `--check`, `--ready`, `--include-archive`, `--browser`, `--follow`, `-f`, `--ascii`, `--mermaid`)\n     - **Trailing flags / missing values (requireValue)**: 22 subprocess tests verifying graceful exit with error message for every value-consuming flag\n     - **Unknown flags**: 6 tests verifying they don't crash or interfere\n     - **Flag collisions**: `-v`→verify vs `version`, `--release`/`--tag`, `-o`/`--output`, `-m`/`--model`, `--desc`/`--description`\n     - **Repeated flags**: Last-value-wins semantics\n     - **Positional arguments**: Assignment rules, boundary cases\n     - **Real-world CLI examples**: 9 tests from the help text\n\n### Verification:\n- ✅ `bun run typecheck` — passes\n- ✅ `bun run build` — passes (0.93 MB bundle)\n- ✅ `bun test tests/arg-parsing.test.ts` — 176 pass, 0 fail","time":{"start":1773435581784,"end":1773435581784}}}
